User Notes:
Kernel versions in the 4.1 and 4.2 series have a broken RAID implementation. If you want to use RAID type LV's, you should install a kernel with version above 4.2.4. Note that several tests use RAID logical volumes, and can generate a kernel oops with faulty kernel version, which usually renders the system unusable.
